# Project Conventions

This rule defines general development conventions for the RevivifAI ESLint configuration project.

## Project Structure

- `src/index.ts` - Main ESLint configuration export
- `eslint.config.js` - Local project ESLint config
- `.cursor/rules/` - Cursor AI rules (this directory)
- `dist/` - Compiled JavaScript output

## Build & Lint Commands

```bash
# Build TypeScript to JavaScript
pnpm run build

# Run linter
pnpm run lint

# Auto-fix lint issues
pnpm run lint:fix

# Full check (lint + build)
pnpm run check
```

## Code Style

- Use 2-space indentation
- Use double quotes for strings
- Always include semicolons
- Use named exports, not default exports
- Follow ESLint stylistic rules from the config

## Git Workflow

- Commit messages should follow conventional commits
- Run `pnpm run check` before pushing
- Keep rules under 500 lines and split if needed

## When Working with Cursor

- Read relevant source files before proposing changes
- Reference existing patterns in the codebase
- Test rules locally before committing
- Update this rule file when patterns change